<div class='function'><span class='function_name'><a class='anchor' id='rating_scale.__init__'>rating_scale</a>.<b>__init__(form, nodes=5, click_accepts=False, var=None)</b></span><div class='details'>
Constructor<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>form</span> &rarr; the parent form
<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Keyword arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>nodes</span> &rarr; the number of nodes or a list of node identifiers (e.g.,
<br />
['yes', 'no', 'maybe']. If a list is passed the rating scale<br />
will have labels, otherwise it will just have boxes.<br />
(default=5)<br />
<span class='variable'>click_accepts</span> &rarr; indicates whether the form should close when a value
<br />
is selected (default=False)<br />
<span class='variable'>var</span> &rarr; the name of the experimental variable that should be used to log
<br />
the widget status (default=None)<br />
</div></div>
